owe our status as a worldclass manufacturer to our employees who continually anticipate and exceed the needs and expectations of all those we work with across the globe at novelis each of us is driven to produce excellence novelis’ employees worldwide are the driving force behind our forwardthinking innovation and its their talent that sets us apart as a twentyfirst century manufacturer we are committed to providing our employees with the opportunities and support they need to further grow their talents and take pride in a diverse team of professionals who represent our unmatched global presence novelis’ worldwide locations enable us to embrace diverse cultures and communities and push boundaries through unique thinking and different perspectives to maximize the experience of our employees we rotate highpotential colleagues through many parts of our business – be it automotive beverage can or highend specialties – in order to prepare them to lead across our global organization our story novelis is the leading producer of flatrolled aluminum products and the world’s largest recycler of aluminum with an integrated network of technically advanced rolling and recycling operations across  facilities in  countries throughout north america south america europe and asia our customers include some of the largest and bestknown automotive beverage can architecture and consumer electronics brands in the world such as cocacola ab inbev ford jaguar land rover and samsung from development to production our worldclass scientists engineers metallurgists and commercial teams partner with our customers to reimagine aluminum’s role in their products and provide rapid adaptive solutions for any manufacturing challenge that may arise novelis was created in  as a spinoff from the canadian aluminum company alcan inc which was established in  in  novelis was acquired by hindalco industries limited and became part of the aditya birla group of companies a  billion multinational conglomerate headquartered in mumbai india search aditya birla jobs a workplace centered around safety within the company novelis set records in fy for safety performance achieving a threeyear low in total recordable incidents as well as improving the number of days away from work rate by more than  percent yearoveryear  as part of our novelis safety system we use a systematic approach for identifying managing and mitigating safety risks in our operations alongside ensuring the health and safety of our employees novelis provides them with opportunities to develop and enhance their skills and grow professionally  this includes encouraging grassrootsled initiatives to make the workplace and our communities safer  one such initiative is novelis prepared where we are working toward  of our colleagues being trained in cpr aed and basic first aid community service working at novelis careers at novelis success beyond the classroom novelis believes today’s students are tomorrow’s leaders whether you’ve just received your bachelor’s degree or you’re working toward an mba all the tools and support you seek are right here to help highpotential college graduates particularly those focused on materials mechanical electrical and automation engineering roles novelis proudly offers our engineering development program edp program this twoyear training program for new graduates helps aspiring engineers accelerate the beginning of an exciting career with us and includes professional and leadership training at one of our  plants around the globe classroom coursework workbased assignments coaching onthejob projects and other development opportunities rotational assignments designed to enhance leadership skills and augment technical abilities career paths upon completion of the program your career path is defined by your interest in a specialty area in alignment with novelis business needs these can include automation engineering reliability engineering process engineering environmental health and safety candidate requirements novelis is looking for the best and brightest minds for this unique opportunity qualified candidates will have bachelor’s or master’s degree in engineering ​mechanical electrical materials sciencemetallurgy computer or information systems solid business acumen minimum gpa of   scale unrestricted work authorization in the country of application regional and global mobility analytical approach to problem solving demonstrated leadership potential engineering profiles at novelis engineering is among the most critical roles in the development of products that are constantly moving aluminum forward and as an engineer here your opportunities to create real impact are numerous and diverse specialized engineering roles where your skills can make a difference at novelis include product metallurgical engineers work extensively with all novelis sheet groups and facilities to ensure production of consistently highquality products metallurgical engineers operate on a sheet and groupwide basis providing technical guidance to all manufacturing and support departments in the areas of product and process metallurgy automation engineers provide expertise in automation computer control and process knowledge and are a critical part of manufacturing particularly in terms of safety quality and cost objectives these positions require a bs degree in computer or information systems experience in the maintenance design development implementation and optimization of automated systems relevant to industrial process control is preferred mechanical engineers provide a full range of engineering expertise effectively servicing equipment buildings grounds and utilities as needed the services provided cover all phases of heavy industrial plant engineering typical of the metals industry and are usually mechanical electrical or civil in nature this role may at times direct the work of outside contractors draftsmen engineering technicians or other elements of the maintenance workforce on special projects electrical engineers provide expertise for project and maintenance work as required to meet the plant’s objectives this can include developing scopes of work schedules and budgets for new equipment or modifications to existing equipment or control systems carrying out engineering studies reviewing and advising on designs developing equipment specifications supervising installations and commissioning and providing cost controls investors  novelis   placeholder investorsnovelis  investors financial strength​ our focus on premium products in established and emerging markets – driven by our model for sustainable manufacturing – is delivering impressive results our solid financial foundation operational excellence and forwardlooking asset allocation strategy is positioning novelis for significant growth​​​​ novelis fact sheet ​ for more information about novelis download the company fact sheet novelis is a global industry leader the world’s leading producer of rolled aluminum product the world’s leading recycler of aluminum global operations spanning  continents please visit the current results tab below to view novelis’ latest financial results and debt tables competitive advantages include focus on premium product unmatched global footprint solid global demand emphasis on sustainability consistent strategy looking for more information about novelis investor relations contact megan cochard director investor relations     megancochardnovelisadityabirlacom corporate governacenews releasescurrent resultshistoric resultssec filingsanalysts coveragepresentations and eventscorporate governace corporate governance novelis leverages strategic longterm thinking and strict adherence to corporate governance principles to drive success and create value for our stakeholders employees and our communities learn more about the guiding forces behind our corporate governance board of directors  board committees leadership and structure code of ethics code of 